  • Classes in et3.java.exceptions used by et3.java.application 
    Class and Description
    DocumentBorrowingException
    Its subclasses are thrown to indicate that the application's user has attempted a borrowing action but something went wrong.
    DocumentNotAvailable
    Thrown to indicate that a Document isn't available from the selected Library.
    EANAlreadyExists
    Thrown to indicate that a Document can't have the same EAN than an existing Document.
    ISBNAlreadyExists
    Thrown to indicate that a Book can't have the same ISBN than an existing Book.
    NoDocumentFound
    Thrown to indicate that no document was found during a research, a borrow, a return or a transfer.
    UnregisteredUser
    Thrown to indicate that a User isn't registred in a selected Library.
